PHASE2:EXPLORATORY DATA ANALYSIS

OBJECTIVE

Our goal is to answer business questions such as:

Why are customers leaving the platform?
Which customer segments are most likely to churn?
How long do customers typically stay active?
What actions can improve customer retention?

Approximately 26.5% of customers have churned while 73.5% remain active. This indicates the overall customer retention performance of the business.

1. Why are customers leaving the platform?

The strongest churn drivers identified so far are:

| Factor                  | Churn Rate |
| ----------------------- | ---------- |
| Fiber Optic Internet    | 41.89% |
| No Tech Support         | 41.64% |
| Month-to-Month Contract | 42.71% |
| DSL Service             | 18.96%     |
| One-Year Contract       | 11.27%     |
| Two-Year Contract       | 2.83%      |

Business Interpretation

Customers are most likely to leave when they:

Have a month-to-month contract.
Lack technical support.
Use Fiber Optic internet services.
Pay higher monthly charges.

2.Which customer segments are most likely to churn?

Based on all analyses so far, the highest-risk segment is:

Customers subscribed to Fiber Optic internet, on month-to-month contracts, without technical support, and paying higher monthly charges.

These customers should be the primary focus of retention strategies.

