Conclusion

The churn analysis revealed that customer attrition is primarily driven by short-term contracts, lack of technical support, fiber optic internet subscriptions, higher monthly charges, and short customer tenure. Customers who remain with the company tend to stay significantly longer and demonstrate stronger loyalty. To improve retention, the company should prioritize converting customers to longer-term contracts, enhancing technical support services, improving the fiber optic customer experience, and implementing targeted retention initiatives during the first year of the customer lifecycle.


